1.26.20  6:57 pm   Hey, Bill! I need some help placing how is it that the chorus for Metallica's Fuel really works at all. The rest of the song it's pretty standard pentatonic/heavy rock pseudo phrygian but then you got that major I chord... with a maj IV and a maj bIII... weird. I mean, I think Cage The Elephant does it too with Back Against The Wall, but I have a hard time relating it to anything theory wise.

     ? seems like you had a pretty easy time just there, relating it to 2 other songs, handily

      Could you help me? Is it just "we placed maj chords over minor pentatonic degrees" or something?

     yes, although i would call it 'we put a 1maj chord where you might have expected a 1min chord to be there, thereby giving you an unexpected dose of happiness and pleasure'

      Cheers! Keep it up!

1.26.20  3:36 pm   I am working on a project with two people, a producer and a rapper, and I think the music is good enough to become successful and I'm really really excited. But I can't help but dread that people won't think it's nearly as good as we do. What do I do to combat this dread? It's making me think I could be insane because I love the music so much, but what if people don't like it and it doesn't get to reach as many ears as I want it to? Maybe I'm overthinking and I shouldn't care? Love your stuff, you inspire me every day

     a good way to avoid this feeling is to do much more stuff, at a more rapid pace. and do it all by yourself so that way you don't have the awkwardness of looking anyone else in the eye and contemplating how much or little you are succeeding. no one has to know, until it's already worked
